All information your child provide will be kept confidential. Only the researchers, and no outside parties, will be able to link your child's identity to the information you provide. We will use a unique study code, and not your child's name on your questionnaire and all other information we gather. We collect your child's name and number for the purpose of contacting them to set up further study visits. Your name and all identifying information will be keep separate from their data with only their unique study code connecting them. The key to decode and connect your child's name and data is kept on a locked server and only study team members have access to it. 

Participation in this screening is voluntary. Should you agree to let your child participate in this study, they are free to withdraw at any time, even after they have already begun. There is no penalty of any kind for withdrawing from this screening form. While we hope they will read each question carefully and provide an honest answer to each, they are free to skip any questions you do not wish to answer. 

