"114","Yalebrowncornell Eating Disorder Scale","MAXED","<div class=""rich-text-field-label""><p>Recent research has shown that preoccupations and rituals commonly occur among people with eating disorders.  While completing the checklist below, please keep in mind our definitions of preoccupations and rituals.</p> <p> </p> <p><strong><u>Preoccupations</u></strong> are <em>ideas, thoughts, images or impulses that repeatedly enter your mind.  They may seem to occur against your will.</em></p> <p style=""tab-stops: .5in;""> </p> <p>Examples of preoccupations might include excessive concern with your body shape, and/or excessive concern about the caloric content of food.</p> <p> </p> <p>Preoccupations differ from worries or concerns.  Worries or concerns tend to just occur from time to time and usually do not affect your life very much, whereas preoccupations may enter your mind so frequently that they interfere with one or more areas of your life.</p> <p> </p> <p><strong><u>Rituals</u></strong>, on the other hand, are <em>behaviors or acts that you feel driven to perform</em>.  At times, you may try to resist doing them but this may prove difficult.  You may experience anxiety that does not diminish until the behavior is completed.</p> <p> </p> <p>An example of a ritual is the need to compute the exact caloric content of all of the foods you consume.  While most rituals are observable behaviors, some are unobservable mental acts, such as silently computing the caloric content of foods, or having to recite nonsense phrases to yourself each time you think of food.</p> <p> </p> <p>Rituals, as we define them here, should not be confused with habits, which most people have.  Habits (e.g., brushing your teeth before washing your face) are routines performed in a similar way.  However, rituals are accompanied with a sense that the activity <em>must</em> be performed in a precise manner.  Altering or being unable to perform a ritual often leads to very unpleasant or anxious feelings.</p></div>; Please identify your Current and Worst periods below:  

